missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/mission-context.md:265:Its core problem is that the missing bridge is also the main difficulty: local near-Beltrami or alignment observables do not obviously control the full stretching quantity, especially the nonlocal remainder. That makes the branch valuable, but comparatively fragile. Its best negative result is useful, though still harder to secure cleanly than Chain 01's shell-based obstruction.
