missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:13:- Chain 03 adds the strongest geometry-first route. It is genuinely different from Chains 01 and 02, it tests a property that averaging is unlikely to preserve intact, and its failure modes are still informative because they isolate whether local Beltrami structure is too fragile or too nonlocal to matter.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:24:3. **Chain 03 - Geometric Vorticity Alignment and Local Beltrami Tubes**
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-step-002-exploration-002.md:7:- Treating Beltrami as a fragility screen rather than a primary survivor stopped the screen from overpromoting the cleanest-looking local geometry.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-step-002-exploration-002.md:11:- Later Tao-screen steps should fix a provisional stretching representation earlier so the "smaller term" can be named less schematically.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-step-002-exploration-002.md:16:For geometry branches, the Tao screen should only let through candidates whose essential content is dynamic coherence, persistence, or a true stretching-facing algebraic link. Static geometry almost always collapses.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:17:- Tool-independent: CZ, IBP, H^1/BMO duality, CRW commutators all give β ≤ 4/3.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:19:- The Lamb vector L = ω × u generates the CZ-lossy pressure piece. For Beltrami flows (L = 0), CZ loss vanishes — but mechanism doesn't survive even 1% perturbation from Beltrami alignment.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:58:3. **First-order vs second-order cancellation.** SQG gains a power via commutator [(-Δ)^{1/2}, u·]θ. NS loses a power through CZ.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:60:SQG in the Caffarelli-Silvestre extension has β = 4/3 (same as NS) at the Chebyshev level. The improvement is entirely in the drift coupling structure, not in beating Chebyshev. This means the question is NOT "how to get β > 4/3" but "how to reformulate the nonlinear interaction so that a different mechanism (commutator-type) handles it."
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:68:3. **Geometric vorticity criteria.** Constantin-Fefferman (1993): regularity holds if vorticity direction is sufficiently regular. Doesn't require De Giorgi at all. Question: can NS dynamics be shown to produce the required vorticity regularity?
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:72:5. **Local Beltrami structure near vortex tubes.** Exact Beltrami kills CZ loss entirely (β_eff → 1.0). The mechanism requires >98% global alignment. But vortex tube cores are locally near-Beltrami. A conditional result using LOCAL Beltrami deficit (restricted to high-|ω| regions) might work — connecting to Constantin-Fefferman geometric criteria.
