missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:1:# Attack on Chain 03 - Geometric Vorticity Alignment and Local Beltrami Tubes
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:7:- local Beltrami alignment (`u` nearly parallel to `omega`)
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:19:- The chosen observables do not naturally feed one another. Small local Beltrami deficit controls `u x omega`, but Constantin-Fefferman type criteria care about spatial regularity of the vorticity direction field. A flow can be pointwise near-Beltrami inside each tube core while `xi` varies wildly from tube to tube or even across nearby filaments.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:20:- "Concentration of the high-|omega| set" is especially weak as a target observable. Concentration is not a regularity mechanism by itself. A highly concentrated vorticity set can still induce bad nonlocal strain, and a diffuse set can still have good alignment.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:22:- The kill condition is too soft. The chain should die not only if known geometric criteria are "too nonlocal," but also if every bridge from local Beltrami deficit to those criteria passes through derivative control of `xi` or some comparably stronger hypothesis. That is not a technical nuisance. That is the obstruction.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:26:### Step 2 - Quantify depletion from local Beltrami structure
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- The anchor case is pointed at the wrong object. Exact Beltrami structure annihilates the Lamb vector `u x omega`, but the dangerous term in the vorticity equation is vortex stretching, i.e. `(omega · grad)u = S omega`. Small `u x omega` does not by itself imply small `S omega` or small `S omega · omega`.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:31:- The step quietly assumes a perturbative principle that the mission context already warns against. Exact Beltrami cancellation is known to be extremely fragile. Localizing the condition to high-vorticity regions does not cure that fragility, because the strain and pressure are nonlocal.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:33:- "Using exact-Beltrami cancellation as the anchor case" risks importing De Giorgi/pressure intuition into a vorticity-stretching problem. The two phenomena are related only indirectly. This step needs a direct path from local alignment to control of `S omega`, not a memory of a different cancellation.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:36:The kill condition again fires too late. If the only estimate available is "local alignment controls a local piece of the stretching," that is already failure, because the unresolved nonlocal remainder is precisely the critical part.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:42:- A statement of the form "if alignment remains controlled on the intense-vorticity set, then blowup is excluded" is not interesting unless the alignment hypothesis is new, scale-appropriate, and plausibly propagated by NS.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:43:- The phrase "identify the exact missing lemma" is too optimistic. The obstruction is unlikely to be one missing lemma. It is more likely a whole package: propagation of local alignment, stability of tube coherence across scales, and a nonlocal estimate that turns deficit control into `S omega` control.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:47:This step should be judged by a much stricter standard: does it create a genuinely new implication from local Beltrami geometry to a known regularity mechanism? If not, it should terminate as a negative result, not be upgraded into a "draft proposition."
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:60:- The chain conflates Beltrami alignment, vorticity-direction coherence, and tube persistence. They are related heuristically, not quantitatively. Treating them as one mechanism is the central structural flaw.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:63:- The success criterion is too forgiving. "Conditional statement or conjecture" is cheap. The chain should count as success only if it proves a new scale-appropriate bridge from local Beltrami deficit to an existing regularity criterion, or else a rigorous obstruction showing why no such bridge exists.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:64:- There is partial prior-art redundancy. Without a hard Beltrami-to-criterion bridge, the chain collapses back into known Constantin-Fefferman style regularity conditions plus suggestive tube language.
