missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:83:Treat it as a short obstruction hunt, not a long proof path. The first question should be whether any scale-critical estimate links local Beltrami deficit on high-`|omega|` sets to control of `S omega` or to a known vorticity-direction criterion. If the answer is no, the right output is a sharp fragility memo: local near-Beltrami geometry is a descriptive feature of vortex tubes, not an operational regularity lever.
