./missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/GOAL.md:7:**Paper:** Alexis Vasseur, "A new proof of partial regularity of solutions to Navier-Stokes equations," *NoDEA: Nonlinear Differential Equations and Applications*, 14(5-6):753-785, 2007.
./promising-findings.md:44:**Why it's unique:** 8 independent derivation paths all converge on the same theory (spectral dimension, entanglement bootstrap, most general renormalizable action, asymptotic freedom, Lee-Wick gravity, asymptotic safety, agravity, Weinberg's program). The minimal axiom set is: Lorentz invariance + diffeomorphism invariance + locality + perturbative renormalizability + unitarity. Relaxing any one opens alternatives; keeping all five forces QG+F.
./promising-findings.md:52:**Honest limits:** This is an existing research program (Anselmi et al., 25+ papers since 2017), not invented by the system. The derivation paths and uniqueness framing are novel contributions. The fakeon is purely virtual and never directly observable.
./promising-findings.md:68:- Inflation reconciliation: both frameworks predict Starobinsky inflation with r ~ 0.003; the pre-existing claim that r discriminates them was shown to be wrong
./promising-findings.md:103:**The result:** The convergence of spectral dimension d_s → 2 across CDT, asymptotic safety, string theory, LQG, Horava-Lifshitz, causal sets, and noncommutative geometry is not coincidental. All these approaches are approximating the same UV physics: quadratic gravity with fakeons. Each captures part of the picture — CDT sees d_s ≈ 2 numerically, asymptotic safety sees anomalous dimension η = 2, strings see 2D thermodynamics, etc.
./promising-findings.md:115:**The result:** The fakeon prescription can be derived independently from modular flow unitarity — an information-theoretic argument. In standard Lee-Wick quantization, ghost particle creation above threshold spoils the positivity of the modular Hamiltonian, violating unitarity. With the fakeon prescription, the ghost is projected out, preserving modular flow unitarity. This gives a novel derivation chain: maximal vacuum entanglement hypothesis + modular flow unitarity → fakeon prescription → QG+F.
./promising-findings.md:211:3. **AF → NGFP trajectory existence** — determine whether a continuous RG trajectory connects the asymptotically free regime to the non-Gaussian fixed point. Tests the structural conjecture itself.
./promising-findings.md:269:**The result:** The classicality budget R_δ ≤ (S_max/S_T − 1)/(1−δ) is a hard upper limit on how many independent observers can verify a classical fact of entropy S_T in a region with maximum entropy S_max. Derived from 5 explicit axioms; the Holevo bound is the essential (previously unremarked) bridge between quantum Darwinism and holographic entropy bounds.
./promising-findings.md:271:**Strongest finding — QD↔HQEC mapping:** Quantum Darwinism (Zurek) and Holographic Quantum Error Correction (Almheiri-Dong-Harlow, HaPPY) are the same phenomenon in different languages. 24 arXiv searches, 15 papers: zero cross-citations between the two communities in 20+ years. The HaPPY code achieves exactly R_δ = S_max/(2·S_T) — 50% of the classicality budget maximum, provable from quantum secret sharing.
./promising-findings.md:293:**HaPPY theorem:** The HaPPY pentagon code achieves R_δ = n/2 = S_max/(2·S_T) — exactly 50% of the classicality budget maximum. Provable from perfect tensor quantum secret sharing.
./promising-findings.md:332:**The observation:** The Hankel determinant saturation ratio det(H₂)/g₂₀² exhibits non-monotonic behavior as a function of UV mass ratio M₂/M₁, reaching maximum deviation from saturation at M₂/M₁ ≈ 1.25–1.50. Could serve as a spectroscopic tool to determine the UV resonance mass ratio from low-energy EFT measurements alone.
./promising-findings.md:362:**Root cause:** The ω³ spectral density of the zero-point field creates a positive feedback loop in any nonlinear system — frequency shifts up → more ZPF power → more energy injection. Harmonic oscillator is immune (fixed frequency). All three proposed SED modifications fail.
./promising-findings.md:364:**Key novel finding — convergence law:** The SED-to-QM residual converges as Δ(⟨x²⟩)/⟨x²⟩_QM ∝ τ^{0.23} × ω_max^{-0.18}. Reducing the residual to 1% would require τ/τ_phys ~ 10^{-100} — physically inaccessible. First numerical SED simulation of the anharmonic oscillator (Pesquera-Claverie 1982 was analytic only).
./promising-findings.md:374:### 18. SED Convergence Law: τ^{0.23} × ω_max^{-0.18}
./promising-findings.md:378:**The result:** For the quartic anharmonic oscillator, SED position variance overshoots QM by 17.8% at β=1. The residual follows a power law in radiation reaction parameter τ and UV cutoff ω_max. Extrapolation: 1% accuracy requires τ/τ_phys ~ 10^{-100} — physically inaccessible. Demonstrates SED failure is not a computational limitation but a structural one.
./promising-findings.md:380:**Evidence:** ALD simulation at 7 coupling strengths (200 trajectories each). Convergence study across multiple (τ, ω_max) pairs. Connected to Santos O(ℏ²) Moyal bracket corrections.
./promising-findings.md:413:**The result:** For non-vacuum states on a Rindler-wedge lattice, modular flow response δC_local(t) has zero spectral weight at the physical mode frequency ω_m, oscillating instead at modular frequencies ε_k/(2π) from the entanglement spectrum. Discrepancy grows N^{0.33} (1-particle) to N^{0.44} (squeezed vacuum) — a genuine continuum feature, not a lattice artifact.
./promising-findings.md:443:**The result:** The β < 1/6 mass gap threshold is numerically correct but the proof has an irreparable gap. The B² formula step (HessS(v,v) = (β/2N)Σ|B□(Q,v)|²) is NOT an identity at generic Q — it's exact only at flat connections. Follow-up validation found λ_max(H_actual) > λ_max(H_formula) for one-hot perturbations at d≥3. The excess is small (≤ 2.6% at d=2, ≤ 0.5% at d=4), so the conclusion is approximately correct.
./promising-findings.md:447:- Staggered mode = tight maximizer at Q=I, λ_max = 4d — PROVED
./promising-findings.md:456:- Flat connections as global maximizers of λ_max(H_actual) — FALSE at all d≥2
./promising-findings.md:460:**Most promising untested path:** Concavity of λ_max(HessS(Q)) on SU(2)^E. Flat connections are strict local maxima with negative-definite second variation. If concavity holds, the bound follows immediately. Code was written but not run.
./promising-findings.md:520:**Weak majorization [TESTED — HOLDS]:** The partial sums of sorted eigenvalues of H(Q) are always dominated by those of H(I). 0 violations in 2300+ samples across d=2,3,4. Margins are comfortable and grow with dimension (0.25 in d=2, 1.5 in d=4). This is now the leading proof strategy — a proof via trace/moment inequalities or Schur convexity is the natural next step.
