./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:63:The real issue is not whether an identity exists, but whether it improves the localized/truncated interaction that blocks the proof. That question appears only in Step 3. Steps 1 and 2 can therefore consume budget on identities that are obviously harmless at the PDE level but useless at the proof level.
