./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:7:The correct refinement is to fix one inherited estimate architecture at the start, define the gain in one bookkeeping currency, require an explicit Tao discriminator, and treat this branch as a bounded test of whether exact NS reformulations or one tightly specified paired auxiliary quantity can beat the named bottleneck. If not, the obstruction memo is the intended success case.
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:17:But this does not make the branch illegitimate. A focused cleanup test of the "maybe an exact rewrite helps inside the current architecture" loophole is still worthwhile. The fix is not to turn this branch into a global discovery program. The fix is to state honestly that it is an obstruction/cleanup branch and to allow at most one tightly specified auxiliary-quantity variant so the negative result is not hard-coded from the start.
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:33:The refined version should therefore say plainly that it is testing a tightly defined family of exact reformulations, while allowing one paired identity or auxiliary propagated quantity if that route is predeclared and still tied to the same target estimate.
