./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:104:Most of that probability lies on a useful negative result: a disciplined memo showing that, within one fixed estimate architecture and a tightly defined candidate family, exact NS reformulations do not produce a Tao-relevant gain except possibly through geometry-dominated or architecture-changing effects. The chance of a genuinely positive lead remains materially lower, but not zero once the chain allows one tightly controlled auxiliary-quantity route.
