./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-001-exploration-002-tao-gate-pressure-branch.md:128:[VERIFIED] Generic harmonic regularity is a dead end here. Harnack, local `H^1`, Campanato, derivative decay, harmonic polynomial approximation, and related elliptic regularity are exactly the kind of tools Tao's averaged model preserves. The chain-01 attack memo says these should be presumed guilty immediately unless attached to an NS-specific identity that acts on `C_far`.
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This chain is pointed at a genuinely relevant axis: NS-specific vortex geometry is a plausible place to look after the De Giorgi and pure harmonic-analysis routes are exhausted. But the chain, as written, leans on an unproved equivalence between three different things:
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:8:- vorticity-direction regularity (`xi = omega / |omega|` is coherent across space)
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:19:- The chosen observables do not naturally feed one another. Small local Beltrami deficit controls `u x omega`, but Constantin-Fefferman type criteria care about spatial regularity of the vorticity direction field. A flow can be pointwise near-Beltrami inside each tube core while `xi` varies wildly from tube to tube or even across nearby filaments.
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:22:- The kill condition is too soft. The chain should die not only if known geometric criteria are "too nonlocal," but also if every bridge from local Beltrami deficit to those criteria passes through derivative control of `xi` or some comparably stronger hypothesis. That is not a technical nuisance. That is the obstruction.
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:24:Fair point: forcing explicit observables early is better than vague "vortex tubes help" rhetoric. But the step needs a harsher test of whether these observables actually talk to existing criteria at all.
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:34:- The hidden assumption is that the intense-vorticity region is where the bad geometry lives and where the right depletion should be measured. But blowup scenarios, if they exist, may be driven by tube bending, inter-tube interaction, or strain generated by the surrounding field rather than by the tube core itself.
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:45:- There is a serious risk of proving only a supercritical or non-operational conditional statement. If the resulting hypothesis is stronger than existing criteria or gives no path to persistence, the chain has not moved the mission forward.
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:63:- The success criterion is too forgiving. "Conditional statement or conjecture" is cheap. The chain should count as success only if it proves a new scale-appropriate bridge from local Beltrami deficit to an existing regularity criterion, or else a rigorous obstruction showing why no such bridge exists.
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:72:- It targets an NS-specific axis that Tao's averaged model plausibly damages.
./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/mission-context.md:19:- The Lamb vector L = ω × u generates the CZ-lossy pressure piece. For Beltrami flows (L = 0), CZ loss vanishes — but mechanism doesn't survive even 1% perturbation from Beltrami alignment.
