+# Meta-Learning: Step 4, Exploration 001 (Primary Hybrid Dynamic Screen)
+
+## What Worked
+
+- Forcing the primary hybrid to answer on one diffusion-scale Eulerian window
+  prevented descriptive tube language from standing in for a propagation
+  mechanism.
+- Reusing the Step-3 package exactly made the hidden assumptions visible:
+  the route's real burden is matching coherent intense components across a
+  moving superlevel set without tube-adapted relocalization.
+- Treating the Tao discriminator and the transport burden separately clarified
+  an important distinction:
+  a candidate can still be Tao-sensitive while being dynamically too weak to
+  justify the next step.
+
+## What Could Be Improved
+
+- Explorer-session monitoring should not infer substantive progress from report
+  skeleton creation.
+- The factual library would benefit from one small note that isolates the
+  direction-field diffusion burden on intense sets, since that burden now
+  recurs across multiple geometry screens.
+
+## Generalizable Lesson
+
+When a candidate's only live content is "dynamic persistence," force it to say
+what survives one diffusion-scale Eulerian window. If the answer is still only
+a heuristic, mark it dynamically weak even if the Tao discriminator remains
+conceptually live.
